Add the chicken or vegetable stock, soy sauce, honey and lime juice to a saucepan and allow to simmer on a low heat.Add the shallot, chilli, pak choi, noodles and chicken breast to the saucepan. Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer gently for 10-12 minutes, until the chicken is thoroughly cooked.Transfer the broth to serving bowls and garnish with coriander leaves to serve.